1
00:00:00,573 --> 00:00:04,413
(The warm spring breeze blows today.)

2
00:00:05,143 --> 00:00:06,712
(It's the recording day for Wanna One's new fan song, )

3
00:00:06,713 --> 00:00:08,843
("Again, Spring Breeze!")

4
00:00:09,283 --> 00:00:10,712
(The members arrive at the recording studio.)

5
00:00:10,713 --> 00:00:11,952
(Kim Jae Hwan)

6
00:00:11,953 --> 00:00:13,383
(Yoon Ji Sung, Bae Jin Young)

7
00:00:13,483 --> 00:00:14,853
Hello.

8
00:00:15,183 --> 00:00:16,753
(Park Ji Hoon)

9
00:00:17,393 --> 00:00:20,293
(And the director of "Again, Spring Breeze," Ha Sung Woon)

10
00:00:20,593 --> 00:00:23,322
(Practicing the high notes endlessly upon arrival)

11
00:00:23,323 --> 00:00:25,263
When we released "Flowerbomb..."

12
00:00:25,833 --> 00:00:27,702
When we released "Flowerbomb," I saw this in the dorm.

13
00:00:27,703 --> 00:00:29,102
(It's like the "Flowerbomb" days. This all seems familiar.)

14
00:00:29,103 --> 00:00:30,872
He kept practicing in the neighboring room.

15
00:00:30,873 --> 00:00:31,873
(Shouting)

16
00:00:31,933 --> 00:00:33,103
This song has higher notes.

17
00:00:33,943 --> 00:00:35,023
Aren't they about the same?

18
00:00:35,143 --> 00:00:36,303
(Let's stay together forever)

19
00:00:37,073 --> 00:00:39,912
It's hard. Recording a song is hard because I get nervous.

20
00:00:39,913 --> 00:00:41,512
When I enter the booth to record a song,

21
00:00:41,513 --> 00:00:43,653
- I can hear my own heartbeat. - Really?

22
00:00:43,883 --> 00:00:44,883
We're pressured to do well.

23
00:00:44,884 --> 00:00:46,753
- It's because of that pressure. - Yes.

24
00:00:47,623 --> 00:00:48,652
(Getting ready to record after warming up his throat)

25
00:00:48,653 --> 00:00:50,053
This is bad.

26
00:00:50,653 --> 00:00:51,893
Gosh, I'm nervous.

27
00:00:53,693 --> 00:00:55,922
(The fan song recording begins in a nervous state.)

28
00:00:55,923 --> 00:00:57,192
I want to record the song well...

29
00:00:57,193 --> 00:00:59,432
so that Wannable will be happy.

30
00:00:59,433 --> 00:01:01,033
(For Wannable who waited for many years)

31
00:01:01,103 --> 00:01:05,033
It'll be our gift to Wannable after seven years.

32
00:01:05,403 --> 00:01:06,473
I'm really excited.

33
00:01:07,573 --> 00:01:09,743
(Nervous)

34
00:01:11,613 --> 00:01:13,272
I'm very nervous.

35
00:01:13,273 --> 00:01:15,482
But I prepared for the recording with excitement in my heart.

36
00:01:15,483 --> 00:01:18,043
(They prepare for the recording in a nervous and excited state.)

37
00:01:18,253 --> 00:01:19,782
(Ji Sung is getting ready to record the song.)

38
00:01:19,783 --> 00:01:21,383
Where is the microphone? Oh, here it is.

39
00:01:21,953 --> 00:01:24,253
(Leader Yoon almost sang with the back of his head.)

40
00:01:24,323 --> 00:01:25,323
He seems nervous.

41
00:01:25,324 --> 00:01:26,893
He seems very nervous.

42
00:01:28,223 --> 00:01:30,023
He hasn't recorded a song in a million years.

43
00:01:30,193 --> 00:01:31,333
Let's begin recording.

44
00:01:33,363 --> 00:01:34,832
(Ji Sung is a bit ahead of the beat.)

45
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:36,433
It didn't sound like you made a promise.

46
00:01:37,403 --> 00:01:38,703
You didn't make a pinky promise.

47
00:01:39,073 --> 00:01:41,602
Take a breath and go, "It's okay."

48
00:01:41,603 --> 00:01:43,403
Make it natural. "It's okay."

49
00:01:43,613 --> 00:01:44,812
"It... It's okay."

50
00:01:44,813 --> 00:01:46,712
- "It's." - It's too high-pitched.

51
00:01:46,713 --> 00:01:48,512
It's okay.

52
00:01:48,513 --> 00:01:50,043
Gosh, it isn't okay.

53
00:01:50,283 --> 00:01:51,952
Ji Sung, you need to hit the high notes.

54
00:01:51,953 --> 00:01:53,513
- Right. - Put your strength into it.

55
00:01:54,123 --> 00:01:56,403
(As Sung Woon has directed, Ji Sung sings with strength.)

56
00:01:56,553 --> 00:01:57,652
That's it.

57
00:01:57,653 --> 00:01:58,653
Ji Sung, are you okay?

58
00:01:58,654 --> 00:02:00,253
(Dad, cheer up.)

59
00:02:00,663 --> 00:02:03,023
(Jin Young is the next one.)

60
00:02:05,763 --> 00:02:06,763
Can I sing it like this?

61
00:02:06,763 --> 00:02:07,763
No, you can't.

62
00:02:07,763 --> 00:02:08,763
(Stern)

63
00:02:08,863 --> 00:02:10,602
- Lose the vibrato for "Past." - Okay.

64
00:02:10,603 --> 00:02:12,772
Sing "Stopped" and "Past" more prettily.

65
00:02:12,773 --> 00:02:14,693
The way you sang "Back and forth" was very nice.

66
00:02:15,273 --> 00:02:16,942
(The charismatic Director Sung Woon)

67
00:02:16,943 --> 00:02:18,712
(The second attempt)

68
00:02:18,713 --> 00:02:20,543
(He understood perfectly.)

69
00:02:20,943 --> 00:02:22,143
(How was it?)

70
00:02:22,243 --> 00:02:23,413
We'll go with this version.

71
00:02:23,613 --> 00:02:25,013
(Jin Young gains confidence.)

72
00:02:25,083 --> 00:02:26,613
- Can you try it? - Yes!

73
00:02:26,753 --> 00:02:28,353
Okay! Sounds good!

74
00:02:29,023 --> 00:02:31,253
(It's Dae Hwi's turn to record.)

75
00:02:34,323 --> 00:02:36,093
Make "Goodbye" a bit shorter.

76
00:02:36,523 --> 00:02:37,663
(He fixes it instantly.)

77
00:02:37,893 --> 00:02:40,533
(It's only a momentary goodbye)

78
00:02:40,703 --> 00:02:42,162
- It was perfect. - How nice.

79
00:02:42,163 --> 00:02:43,163
Listen.

80
00:02:43,164 --> 00:02:45,049
(Dae Hwi receives compliments and finishes recording.)

81
00:02:45,073 --> 00:02:47,403
(This time, Ji Hoon records his part.)

82
00:02:50,873 --> 00:02:53,042
- When you sing, "Calls," - Okay.

83
00:02:53,043 --> 00:02:54,582
Think of it as a staircase.

84
00:02:54,583 --> 00:02:55,942
When the spring breeze calls.

85
00:02:55,943 --> 00:02:58,712
Imagine putting "Calls" gently on the top.

86
00:02:58,713 --> 00:02:59,783
- Let's try it. - Okay.

87
00:03:00,213 --> 00:03:01,382
(The 2nd attempt)

88
00:03:01,383 --> 00:03:02,453
(Singing)

89
00:03:03,353 --> 00:03:04,423
Well done.

90
00:03:04,723 --> 00:03:05,723
Okay.

91
00:03:05,724 --> 00:03:07,324
(Ji Hoon records his part successfully!)

92
00:03:08,263 --> 00:03:12,393
(Min Hyun's recording goes smoothly as well.)

93
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:17,573
(It's time for Seong Wu, the member who was worried from the start.)

94
00:03:17,733 --> 00:03:18,733
Hey, that's good.

95
00:03:18,734 --> 00:03:20,233
- Is that good? - Yes.

96
00:03:20,603 --> 00:03:21,972
- Thank you. - Shall we go with this version?

97
00:03:21,973 --> 00:03:23,573
- Yes. - My goodness.

98
00:03:23,813 --> 00:03:25,813
(It's Wanna One's main vocalist, Jae Hwan's turn.)

99
00:03:28,743 --> 00:03:29,743
How nice.

100
00:03:29,744 --> 00:03:30,982
Jae Hwan, it was perfect.

101
00:03:30,983 --> 00:03:32,652
Sung Woon, I made "Passes" a bit throaty.

102
00:03:32,653 --> 00:03:34,152
I added a bit of Bruno Mars' vibes.

103
00:03:34,153 --> 00:03:35,683
(Just a bit)

104
00:03:35,783 --> 00:03:37,252
I thought it was the actual Bruno Mars.

105
00:03:37,253 --> 00:03:38,253
Thank you.

106
00:03:38,823 --> 00:03:40,593
(Jjaeruno Mars continues to do well.)

107
00:03:40,923 --> 00:03:43,392
(Explosive high notes)

108
00:03:43,393 --> 00:03:44,393
Perfect.

109
00:03:45,493 --> 00:03:49,263
(He easily sings the numerous high-pitched parts.)

110
00:03:50,063 --> 00:03:51,232
Singing that part felt good, right?

111
00:03:51,233 --> 00:03:52,233
It was a bit tasty.

112
00:03:52,234 --> 00:03:54,372
That's what matters. It comes down to whether it felt good.

113
00:03:54,373 --> 00:03:56,002
- It was tasty. - All right.

114
00:03:56,003 --> 00:03:57,213
I'm full.

115
00:03:58,413 --> 00:04:00,883
(Wanna One's main rapper, Woo Jin goes next.)

116
00:04:03,343 --> 00:04:04,829
- Let me listen to it once more. - Okay.

117
00:04:04,853 --> 00:04:06,783
Woo Jin wrote the rap verses.

118
00:04:07,883 --> 00:04:11,122
By writing the rap verses myself, I could do a better job...

119
00:04:11,123 --> 00:04:12,823
of expressing my feelings for Wannable.

120
00:04:18,733 --> 00:04:20,139
What I did just now was pretty good.

121
00:04:20,163 --> 00:04:22,603
I'll need to record my part again since they've done so well.

122
00:04:23,803 --> 00:04:28,943
(The songwriter, Sung Woon's re-recording comes last!)

123
00:04:29,873 --> 00:04:32,743
(The recording of the fan song, "Again, Spring Breeze," is done.)

124
00:04:33,673 --> 00:04:34,683
Post-credits scene.

125
00:04:35,183 --> 00:04:37,653
(While Vero's dad, Ji Sung records his part...)

126
00:04:37,713 --> 00:04:39,353
Vero, do you want a snack?

127
00:04:39,983 --> 00:04:42,083
(Vero stares at the door Ji Sung has walked out of.)

128
00:04:42,583 --> 00:04:44,552
(Jin Young picks him up and moves him in the end.)

129
00:04:44,553 --> 00:04:45,553
Vero, stay here.

130
00:04:45,554 --> 00:04:46,622
(Jin Young picks him up and moves him in the end.)

131
00:04:46,623 --> 00:04:50,433
Vero, why are you so scared?

132
00:04:51,063 --> 00:04:52,092
(Befriending Vero, Stage 1: Pat Vero's chin.)

133
00:04:52,093 --> 00:04:53,533
(Happy)

134
00:04:53,903 --> 00:04:56,563
(Befriending Vero, Stage 2: Give Vero a cockscomb.)

135
00:04:56,903 --> 00:04:58,449
(Befriending Vero, Stage 3: Communicate with a dog's language.)

136
00:04:58,473 --> 00:04:59,773
(You're too much.)

137
00:05:00,203 --> 00:05:02,673
(Staring)

138
00:05:04,113 --> 00:05:05,113
(Touching)

139
00:05:05,773 --> 00:05:07,643
(Put me on your lap.)

140
00:05:09,483 --> 00:05:10,813
(Comfortable)

141
00:05:11,253 --> 00:05:15,382
(Bae Bae and Vero succeed in becoming close!)

142
00:05:15,383 --> 00:05:17,652
("Again, Spring Breeze" will be released...)

143
00:05:17,653 --> 00:05:19,923
(on various music platforms at 6pm on May 20.)

144
00:05:32,903 --> 00:05:34,773
(Bae Bae's Camera, Updates and Go)

145
00:05:35,073 --> 00:05:36,073
Hello.

146
00:05:36,443 --> 00:05:39,343
Are you enjoying "WANNA ONE GO: Back to Base?"

147
00:05:39,613 --> 00:05:42,282
"Jin Young, say something" has become a meme.

148
00:05:42,283 --> 00:05:43,442
Jin Young, say something.

149
00:05:43,443 --> 00:05:45,513
I say a lot.

150
00:05:46,713 --> 00:05:49,123
I'm someone who wants a lot of screen time.

151
00:05:49,453 --> 00:05:50,453
Isn't it unexpected?

152
00:05:50,454 --> 00:05:51,599
(Jin Young wanted a lot of screen time.)

153
00:05:51,623 --> 00:05:53,092
Didn't I give good reactions?

154
00:05:53,093 --> 00:05:54,093
I give good reactions.

155
00:05:54,823 --> 00:05:57,833
(The one who wanted a lot of screen time, Jin Young, )

156
00:05:58,333 --> 00:06:01,533
(gave reactions loudly...)

157
00:06:01,833 --> 00:06:07,273
(and smiled from ear to ear while looking at the members.)

158
00:06:07,643 --> 00:06:10,003
As Wannable wants,

159
00:06:10,203 --> 00:06:12,213
I'll try to talk a lot.

160
00:06:12,473 --> 00:06:13,543
Please watch me.

161
00:06:14,743 --> 00:06:17,143
(It's a lovely day. Where is Bae Bae going?)

162
00:06:17,353 --> 00:06:19,913
I'm on my way to an event.

163
00:06:20,183 --> 00:06:22,452
This is the first event in a while,

164
00:06:22,453 --> 00:06:24,593
so I'm very excited. I think it'll be fun.

165
00:06:25,223 --> 00:06:26,653
I'll work hard.

166
00:06:27,593 --> 00:06:32,493
(Being a photo shoot master, he poses for photos expertly.)

167
00:06:32,633 --> 00:06:34,632
I've unlocked my beauty.

168
00:06:34,633 --> 00:06:35,633
(He gets interviewed perfectly during the event.)

169
00:06:35,633 --> 00:06:36,633
What do you think?

170
00:06:36,634 --> 00:06:39,773
(Bae Bae's beautiful looks worked hard at the event venue.)

171
00:06:39,973 --> 00:06:41,242
Thanks to the nice weather...

172
00:06:41,243 --> 00:06:42,572
and the pretty venue,

173
00:06:42,573 --> 00:06:44,173
I did well.

174
00:06:44,513 --> 00:06:46,073
My story ends here.

175
00:06:46,773 --> 00:06:48,243
Bye.

176
00:06:48,913 --> 00:06:50,852
Hello, I'm Yoon Ji Sung.

177
00:06:50,853 --> 00:06:54,852
I'm on my way to "Hyojung's Volume Up."

178
00:06:54,853 --> 00:06:57,353
I'll film everything I do there.

179
00:06:57,823 --> 00:06:59,953
- Hello. - Welcome.

180
00:07:00,193 --> 00:07:02,663
At the studio, I check the script first.

181
00:07:02,893 --> 00:07:04,863
- Did I sound too fake? - You sounded too fake.

182
00:07:05,133 --> 00:07:06,763
- Did I sound too fake? - Yes, you did.

183
00:07:07,463 --> 00:07:08,832
- You didn't bring Vero, did you? - No.

184
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:10,462
(Hyojung is very disappointed that Vero hasn't come.)

185
00:07:10,463 --> 00:07:11,903
Hyojung, you're so disappointed.

186
00:07:12,973 --> 00:07:14,442
Hello, I'm...

187
00:07:14,443 --> 00:07:17,172
Ji Sung's DJ friend.

188
00:07:17,173 --> 00:07:20,572
Shouldn't Wanna One get invited to "Volume Up?"

189
00:07:20,573 --> 00:07:22,342
I'll invite the group. Make sure to come.

190
00:07:22,343 --> 00:07:24,512
Okay. We'll wait for the invite.

191
00:07:24,513 --> 00:07:25,852
Yoon Ji Sung, hello.

192
00:07:25,853 --> 00:07:28,122
Hello, I'm Yoon Ji Sung of Wanna One.

193
00:07:28,123 --> 00:07:31,992
Gosh, he began adding "Wanna One" to his introduction.

194
00:07:31,993 --> 00:07:33,752
- The theme song has been released. - Has it been released?

195
00:07:33,753 --> 00:07:35,892
- Yes. So I need to promote it. - You need to work hard.

196
00:07:35,893 --> 00:07:37,492
- Please listen to it. - Okay.

197
00:07:37,493 --> 00:07:39,532
Let's listen to the next story after the song.

198
00:07:39,533 --> 00:07:41,503
It's "WE WANNA GO" by Wanna One.

199
00:07:42,163 --> 00:07:44,579
(It's the OST of "WANNA ONE GO" with the group's love for Wannable.)

200
00:07:44,603 --> 00:07:46,709
(Listening to the song with Wannable makes the time more meaningful.)

201
00:07:46,733 --> 00:07:48,102
It's a song we've released after a long hiatus,

202
00:07:48,103 --> 00:07:50,342
so please listen to it a lot.

203
00:07:50,343 --> 00:07:52,772
- He might like Listener 4399. - What?

204
00:07:52,773 --> 00:07:54,742
All of us were someone's first love.

205
00:07:54,743 --> 00:07:56,512
Please participate in it.

206
00:07:56,513 --> 00:07:58,513
My schedule for the day is done.

207
00:07:58,783 --> 00:07:59,783
(Spotting someone)

208
00:07:59,883 --> 00:08:01,123
- Ji Sung! - Hey!

209
00:08:01,553 --> 00:08:02,553
(Who is it?)

210
00:08:02,553 --> 00:08:03,553
Hello.

211
00:08:03,554 --> 00:08:06,052
Hello. I'm filming for "WANNA ONE GO."

212
00:08:06,053 --> 00:08:08,492
Seriously, my heart ached when I saw Ji Sung cry.

213
00:08:08,493 --> 00:08:10,522
- Do you watch "WANNA ONE GO?" - Yes, I do.

214
00:08:10,523 --> 00:08:12,332
- For the members? - Of course.

215
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:14,162
You're getting a call.

216
00:08:14,163 --> 00:08:16,332
- This one hasn't called in a while. - Right. You should take it.

217
00:08:16,333 --> 00:08:18,632
You're busy. I can tell that you're the celebrity. Okay.

218
00:08:18,633 --> 00:08:20,532
My schedule for the day is over.

219
00:08:20,533 --> 00:08:24,342
I'll see you on "WANNA ONE GO."

220
00:08:24,343 --> 00:08:26,172
Wannable, bye.

221
00:08:26,173 --> 00:08:27,733
(Jirung's Camera, Updates and Go ends!)

222
00:08:32,283 --> 00:08:33,483
Wanna be the one!

223
00:08:33,813 --> 00:08:34,823
What should we do?

224
00:08:35,083 --> 00:08:36,182
(Team Pink Sausage checks out the updated Activity Zone.)

225
00:08:36,183 --> 00:08:37,282
- There are new things. - Yes.

226
00:08:37,283 --> 00:08:39,022
"Instead of using your hands,"

227
00:08:39,023 --> 00:08:40,653
"use your body to bounce the ball."

228
00:08:41,423 --> 00:08:43,192
(New item, ball-catching toy)

229
00:08:43,193 --> 00:08:45,463
You put this on and...

230
00:08:48,303 --> 00:08:49,962
What are you doing?

231
00:08:49,963 --> 00:08:50,973
This is how you do it.

232
00:08:52,103 --> 00:08:54,673
(Onlookers gather upon hearing the news.)

233
00:08:55,173 --> 00:08:58,042
- You send it up like this. - What are you doing?

234
00:08:58,043 --> 00:09:00,003
- Woo Jin, what's going on? - What are you doing?

235
00:09:00,573 --> 00:09:02,213
(What are you doing?)

236
00:09:02,343 --> 00:09:03,643
Is that how you do it?

237
00:09:04,053 --> 00:09:05,173
(He can't believe his eyes.)

238
00:09:05,953 --> 00:09:07,112
(I'm Wanna One's main dancer.)

239
00:09:07,113 --> 00:09:08,122
- Gosh! - What?

240
00:09:08,123 --> 00:09:11,123
Gosh, that's too...

241
00:09:11,793 --> 00:09:13,592
- It looks so dirty. - It's strange.

242
00:09:13,593 --> 00:09:15,292
- That's too... - It looks so dirty.

243
00:09:15,293 --> 00:09:16,762
- It's strange. - Is that...

244
00:09:16,763 --> 00:09:18,603
(Amidst criticism, he finally succeeds in it!)

245
00:09:19,993 --> 00:09:21,532
Is it supposed to look that vulgar?

246
00:09:21,533 --> 00:09:22,633
This is how you do it.

247
00:09:22,903 --> 00:09:25,533
One more time!

248
00:09:25,833 --> 00:09:26,833
Hey.

249
00:09:27,073 --> 00:09:28,972
Shall we try the boxing machine to help with digestion?

250
00:09:28,973 --> 00:09:29,973
Good idea.

251
00:09:30,243 --> 00:09:31,512
Woo Jin, we have more game machines now.

252
00:09:31,513 --> 00:09:33,813
- That's new. - It's a boxing machine.

253
00:09:34,043 --> 00:09:35,943
Okay. Let's try the boxing machine.

254
00:09:36,513 --> 00:09:38,912
Shall we have a match? My punches are really strong.

255
00:09:38,913 --> 00:09:40,953
I'm serious. You guys can't beat me.

256
00:09:41,253 --> 00:09:44,152
Let's determine the king of punches.

257
00:09:44,153 --> 00:09:45,692
- No messing with the winner. - No messing with him.

258
