00:18:07,353 --> 00:18:09,862
- Let's make gimbap as he does it. - Let's go and make gimbap.

519
00:18:09,863 --> 00:18:11,063
Hold on a second.

520
00:18:11,293 --> 00:18:12,493
Both of them are for one hand.

521
00:18:13,193 --> 00:18:14,662
(It makes the matters worse.)

522
00:18:14,663 --> 00:18:16,602
Hold on. What's going on?

523
00:18:16,603 --> 00:18:18,402
They aren't for one person,

524
00:18:18,403 --> 00:18:19,403
- but two. - I see.

525
00:18:19,404 --> 00:18:21,232
- I see. - Wear one each.

526
00:18:21,233 --> 00:18:23,372
- Turn the lever together. - Okay.

527
00:18:23,373 --> 00:18:25,442
- Okay. We'll do it together. - Okay.

528
00:18:25,443 --> 00:18:26,712
Set, go.

529
00:18:26,713 --> 00:18:29,542
- Euratgotcha! - Euratgotcha!

530
00:18:29,543 --> 00:18:30,643
How nice.

531
00:18:32,183 --> 00:18:33,712
- It's an orange one. - An orange one?

532
00:18:33,713 --> 00:18:34,882
- I have a good feeling about it. - Hold on.

533
00:18:34,883 --> 00:18:36,082
- It's so heavy. - Really?

534
00:18:36,083 --> 00:18:37,452
- Hey, it must be meat. - It has to be meat.

535
00:18:37,453 --> 00:18:38,892
- They can barely lift it up. - It's so heavy.

536
00:18:38,893 --> 00:18:40,452
- It's so heavy. - Is it that heavy?

537
00:18:40,453 --> 00:18:44,192
- Hold on. It's really heavy. - It's true. It's really heavy.

538
00:18:44,193 --> 00:18:46,033
- What is it? Open it. - It's open.

539
00:18:47,193 --> 00:18:48,203
What is it?

540
00:18:49,003 --> 00:18:50,432
- It's for a barbecue. - It's meat!

541
00:18:50,433 --> 00:18:52,103
- It's meat! - It's meat!

542
00:18:52,903 --> 00:18:54,303
(Stomping in happiness)

543
00:18:55,103 --> 00:18:56,372
- Korean beef! - It's meat!

544
00:18:56,373 --> 00:18:58,573
It's meat!

545
00:18:59,043 --> 00:19:01,712
"Go to the outdoor Barbecue Zone and enjoy a meat party."

546
00:19:01,713 --> 00:19:03,282
Was it a good idea to get this now?

547
00:19:03,283 --> 00:19:05,052
One group can make gimbap, and the other group can grill meat.

548
00:19:05,053 --> 00:19:06,253
Okay. I'll grill meat.

549
00:19:06,483 --> 00:19:08,182
- I'll make gimbap. - I'll make gimbap.

550
00:19:08,183 --> 00:19:09,482
- I'll grill meat. - Okay.

551
00:19:09,483 --> 00:19:11,123
- I'll work on the charcoal. - Okay.

552
00:19:11,253 --> 00:19:13,453
- You're Team Meat. - I'll grill meat.

553
00:19:13,653 --> 00:19:15,563
(Team Barbecue, Team Gimbap)

554
00:19:15,863 --> 00:19:17,792
- Let's work in the middle. - Let's work here.

555
00:19:17,793 --> 00:19:18,862
- I'll bring the ingredients. - Okay.

556
00:19:18,863 --> 00:19:20,992
There are tuna and mayonnaise as well.

557
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:22,063
There is rice here.

558
00:19:22,603 --> 00:19:24,062
Pickled radish, sausage...

559
00:19:24,063 --> 00:19:25,073
(Getting the ingredients)

560
00:19:25,473 --> 00:19:26,473
Cheese.

561
00:19:26,873 --> 00:19:28,472
- There is cheese as well. - Let's add cheese as well.

562
00:19:28,473 --> 00:19:30,072
What else can we add?

563
00:19:30,073 --> 00:19:31,642
- There is squid as well. - Squid is a good ingredient.

564
00:19:31,643 --> 00:19:32,772
Fish jerky and squid.

565
00:19:32,773 --> 00:19:33,773
Add fishcake.

566
00:19:33,774 --> 00:19:35,543
That's right. I'll add fishcake.

567
00:19:36,783 --> 00:19:38,882
Gosh, there are abundant ingredients.

568
00:19:38,883 --> 00:19:40,383
Will you add that to gimbap?

569
00:19:41,253 --> 00:19:43,253
Roll gimbap!

570
00:19:43,783 --> 00:19:44,922
Is this enough rice?

571
00:19:44,923 --> 00:19:46,293
Cover half of the dried laver.

572
00:19:46,423 --> 00:19:48,222
- I prefer the thin rice layer. - It should be thin.

573
00:19:48,223 --> 00:19:49,963
- Carrot? - I'll add carrot.

574
00:19:50,463 --> 00:19:51,463
Of course.

575
00:19:51,863 --> 00:19:53,733
- I'll add fish jerky. - All right.

576
00:19:54,093 --> 00:19:55,213
I need to add an egg omelet.

577
00:19:56,003 --> 00:19:57,003
Cheese gimbap.

578
00:19:57,463 --> 00:19:59,633
Roll it like that. There you go.

579
00:19:59,903 --> 00:20:01,872
We're pretty skilled at this.

580
00:20:01,873 --> 00:20:04,172
(Team Gimbap is sailing smoothly against everyone's expectations.)

581
00:20:04,173 --> 00:20:05,813
Jin Young, have you rolled gimbap before?

582
00:20:06,043 --> 00:20:07,112
Me? I've done it with Mom...

583
00:20:07,113 --> 00:20:08,142
- when I was a baby. - It's my first time.

584
00:20:08,143 --> 00:20:10,583
Hey, you're still a baby. Were you more of a baby then?

585
00:20:10,713 --> 00:20:12,352
- Yes. - How old were you?

586
00:20:12,353 --> 00:20:14,013
- I was vibrant. - You were vibrant?

587
00:20:14,483 --> 00:20:15,583
You were lively.

588
00:20:15,853 --> 00:20:17,752
Tell me what you want to eat.

589
00:20:17,753 --> 00:20:19,152
I like tuna gimbap.

590
00:20:19,153 --> 00:20:20,952
I'll make it. I'll make tuna gimbap.

591
00:20:20,953 --> 00:20:21,962
He likes basic gimbap.

592
00:20:21,963 --> 00:20:23,362
I don't add tuna. I like basic gimbap.

593
00:20:23,363 --> 00:20:24,363
Come to me for tuna gimbap, Jin Young.

594
00:20:24,364 --> 00:20:25,893
Then I'll go to Jae Hwan.

595
00:20:26,193 --> 00:20:27,632
Tuna gimbap is the best.

596
00:20:27,633 --> 00:20:28,702
- I agree. - Yes.

597
00:20:28,703 --> 00:20:30,762
(1. Spread rice thinly on top of dried laver.)

598
00:20:30,763 --> 00:20:33,833
(2. Add a generous amount of various ingredients.)

599
00:20:34,073 --> 00:20:37,273
(3. Add a lot of tuna, which is Jin Young's favorite.)

600
00:20:37,443 --> 00:20:40,013
(4. Roll it up.)

601
00:20:40,643 --> 00:20:41,782
- Hey. - How does it look?

602
00:20:41,783 --> 00:20:43,712
- Hey, how does it look? - How does it look?

603
00:20:43,713 --> 00:20:45,753
(Success)

604
00:20:46,083 --> 00:20:47,352
I want to try Jae Hwan's gimbap.

605
00:20:47,353 --> 00:20:48,553
Go ahead and try it.

606
00:20:48,583 --> 00:20:50,053
(Jin Young slices it.)

607
00:20:51,423 --> 00:20:52,653
What's this?

608
00:20:53,523 --> 00:20:54,963
Those pieces died.

609
00:20:55,363 --> 00:20:57,262
(Open wide.)

610
00:20:57,263 --> 00:20:58,263
(Eating)

611
00:21:00,733 --> 00:21:01,802
- Is it tasty? - Yes.

612
00:21:01,803 --> 00:21:02,803
(It's a beautiful taste.)

613
00:21:02,804 --> 00:21:04,773
(Let me try it as well.)

614
00:21:05,533 --> 00:21:06,673
- It's tasty. - It's tasty.

615
00:21:06,703 --> 00:21:08,702
- Is it good? - Hey, open a gimbap place.

616
00:21:08,703 --> 00:21:10,073
- Okay. - My goodness.

617
00:21:10,273 --> 00:21:11,742
I'll open a gimbap paradise.

618
00:21:11,743 --> 00:21:14,089
(Will a gimbap place come after a cotton candy shop, gym, and bar?)

619
00:21:14,113 --> 00:21:17,183
(How is Team Barbecue doing in the stormy weather?)

620
00:21:18,353 --> 00:21:20,713
Let's get to work right away. Where are the tongs?

621
00:21:21,553 --> 00:21:22,782
Tongs.

622
00:21:22,783 --> 00:21:24,152
Beef should be eaten...

623
00:21:24,153 --> 00:21:25,629
- right after grilling. - That's right.

624
00:21:25,653 --> 00:21:27,753
(There are different kinds and cuts.)

625
00:21:28,023 --> 00:21:29,463
- Shall we grill pork? - Pork.

626
00:21:29,593 --> 00:21:31,593
Pig! Oh, that came out wrong.

627
00:21:32,293 --> 00:21:34,033
(Pink sausage, not pig)

628
00:21:34,193 --> 00:21:35,702
Do you want to grill pork belly here?

629
00:21:35,703 --> 00:21:37,932
- Okay. - Sounds good. Ji Hoon, let's go.

630
00:21:37,933 --> 00:21:40,633
Show us who you are.

631
00:21:41,173 --> 00:21:42,442
Who am I?

632
00:21:42,443 --> 00:21:43,502
Weren't you an army cook?

633
00:21:43,503 --> 00:21:44,843
- I was an army cook. - Exactly.

634
00:21:45,013 --> 00:21:46,112
Show us.

635
00:21:46,113 --> 00:21:48,089
(That's right. I was an army cook who became legendary!)

636
00:21:48,113 --> 00:21:49,382
(Legendary army cook's skills: Grill pork belly evenly.)

637
00:21:49,383 --> 00:21:50,983
- I'll show you. - Okay.

638
00:21:51,953 --> 00:21:54,353
- I'll stay here and give orders. - Okay.

639
00:21:55,183 --> 00:21:56,582
(I can't wait to see the army cook's work.)

640
00:21:56,583 --> 00:21:58,822
It'll be hard to grill pork belly.

641
00:21:58,823 --> 00:22:00,252
- Shall I do it? - We should work together.

642
00:22:00,253 --> 00:22:02,533
- I'm really good at it. - Look. The lard caught on fire.

643
00:22:04,223 --> 00:22:05,532
He has no skills.

644
00:22:05,533 --> 00:22:06,562
(Pork belly is on fire.)

645
00:22:06,563 --> 00:22:08,733
It's falling.

646
00:22:08,763 --> 00:22:10,062
- He has no skills. - Hey.

647
00:22:10,063 --> 00:22:12,233
I was sorting things out.

648
00:22:12,673 --> 00:22:14,553
- I was sorting things out. - He has no skills.

649
00:22:14,603 --> 00:22:15,903
It's because of the lard.

650
00:22:16,273 --> 00:22:18,212
- You need to do it on the side. - Go over there.

651
00:22:18,213 --> 00:22:19,612
(On top of that, he gets attacked by the smoke.)

652
00:22:19,613 --> 00:22:22,843
(Meanwhile)

653
00:22:23,213 --> 00:22:25,382
- What is this onion for? - I'll do it.

654
00:22:25,383 --> 00:22:26,753
Shall we grill onions too?

655
00:22:26,853 --> 00:22:28,183
Do it here.

656
00:22:29,353 --> 00:22:30,883
The fat is dripping.

657
00:22:32,423 --> 00:22:34,823
It's falling.

658
00:22:35,363 --> 00:22:37,362
It's falling. Come on.

659
00:22:37,363 --> 00:22:38,609
(He adds sausages to the grill before meat.)

660
00:22:38,633 --> 00:22:40,363
(I love sausages.)

661
00:22:40,633 --> 00:22:43,163
(A bit later)

662
00:22:44,233 --> 00:22:45,932
Seong Wu, you added sausages too early on.

663
00:22:45,933 --> 00:22:47,333
(Seong Wu's sausages turn to soot.)

664
00:22:47,533 --> 00:22:48,902
I can't see.

665
00:22:48,903 --> 00:22:51,173
(Smoke from the sausages attacks the sparrow.)

666
00:22:51,343 --> 00:22:52,473
(Seong Wu caused trouble.)

667
00:22:52,673 --> 00:22:54,513
Shall we keep the sausages here?

668
00:22:55,713 --> 00:22:56,743
It's hot.

669
00:22:57,183 --> 00:23:00,313
(To make matters worse, the rain gets heavier.)

670
00:23:01,113 --> 00:23:03,582
Hey, this is water.

671
00:23:03,583 --> 00:23:04,723
(Water pools on the tarp.)

672
00:23:05,223 --> 00:23:06,623
Camping in the rain...

673
00:23:08,893 --> 00:23:09,993
Gosh, it's cold.

674
00:23:10,023 --> 00:23:11,393
This won't fall over, right?

675
00:23:11,963 --> 00:23:12,963
(Screaming)

676
00:23:13,733 --> 00:23:15,233
(It's a water bomb.)

677
00:23:15,763 --> 00:23:17,203
Gosh, Woo Jin!

678
00:23:17,833 --> 00:23:19,273
Woo Jin, the meat is burning!

679
00:23:20,703 --> 00:23:22,172
(The meat burns.)

680
00:23:22,173 --> 00:23:23,303
Gosh, it's hot!

681
00:23:23,803 --> 00:23:24,972
We could've cooked pork belly on this cauldron lid.

682
00:23:24,973 --> 00:23:26,242
Is there water? We just need to sprinkle some water.

683
00:23:26,243 --> 00:23:27,919
- Should we have cooked it here? - Gosh, it's hot!

684
00:23:27,943 --> 00:23:28,982
(Amidst chaos, one thought enters his mind.)

685
00:23:28,983 --> 00:23:31,182
I wonder if people inside know...

686
00:23:31,183 --> 00:23:33,453
about this situation.

687
00:23:34,753 --> 00:23:36,473
They must be rolling gimbap without a care.

688
00:23:38,293 --> 00:23:40,193
(Correct)

689
00:23:41,193 --> 00:23:44,963
(They roll gimbap in a classy manner and eat a piece at a time.)

690
00:23:45,763 --> 00:23:47,692
- Jae Hwan can roll gimbap well. - I know.

691
00:23:47,693 --> 00:23:48,962
- I can roll gimbap well. - He wasn't only good at singing.

692
00:23:48,963 --> 00:23:50,863
I had no idea that I could roll gimbap well.

693
00:23:51,433 --> 00:23:54,602
Jae Hwan, would you make a buldak gimbap?

694
00:23:54,603 --> 00:23:56,072
- Okay. - Tuna buldak.

695
00:23:56,073 --> 00:23:57,303
Tuna buldak?

696
00:23:59,243 --> 00:24:02,842
(Adding the buldak sauce of horror)

697
00:24:02,843 --> 00:24:03,982
Jae Hwan, add more.

698
00:24:03,983 --> 00:24:05,312
It'll cause a stomachache.

699
00:24:05,313 --> 00:24:06,482
I won't eat it anyway.

700
00:24:06,483 --> 00:24:07,982
Tuna will lessen the blow.

701
00:24:07,983 --> 00:24:10,022
(He squeezes in the sauce without holding back.)

702
00:24:10,023 --> 00:24:11,622
- Everyone likes buldak. - That's right.

703
00:24:11,623 --> 00:24:13,023
This isn't bullying.

704
00:24:13,723 --> 00:24:14,752
It smells evil.

705
00:24:14,753 --> 00:24:16,593
I know. I can smell the spicy sauce from here.

706
00:24:17,293 --> 00:24:19,062
(His breath turns ragged.)

707
00:24:19,063 --> 00:24:21,292
(Breathing in and out)

708
00:24:21,293 --> 00:24:22,402
(Breathing in and out)

709
00:24:22,403 --> 00:24:24,802
- It seems like something scary. - I know. It looks lethal.

710
00:24:24,803 --> 00:24:25,902
It looks so scary.

711
00:24:25,903 --> 00:24:26,903
I know.

712
00:24:26,904 --> 00:24:28,372
(Jae Hwan breathes heavily.)

713
00:24:28,373 --> 00:24:31,673
(The gimbap net and gloves are colored red.)

714
00:24:31,943 --> 00:24:33,113
He is absorbed.

715
00:24:34,073 --> 00:24:36,059
(With the spicy aroma, buldak tuna gimbap is done.)

716
00:24:36,083 --> 00:24:38,352
- Buldak gimbap is no joke. - I know.

717
00:24:38,353 --> 00:24:40,513
- It'll be really spicy. - We'll make them poop blood.

718
00:24:41,413 --> 00:24:43,653
(Back to Team Barbecue in the heavy rain)

719
00:24:44,523 --> 00:24:47,623
(Thankfully, meat is getting cooked nicely.)

720
00:24:48,863 --> 00:24:51,292
This looks legit. It needs to be eaten now.

721
00:24:51,293 --> 00:24:52,733
Hey, should we eat it?

722
00:24:53,463 --> 00:24:55,402
Hey, it's game over.

723
00:24:55,403 --> 00:24:58,032
- Seriously, Sung Woon. - Oh, my!

724
00:24:58,033 --> 00:24:59,603
Sung Woon! Come on!

725
00:25:02,473 --> 00:25:04,303
(He picked up the meat to brag.)

726
00:25:05,573 --> 00:25:07,243
(Falling)

727
00:25:07,543 --> 00:25:09,043
(I must save it.)

728
00:25:09,513 --> 00:25:10,513
(Bye.)

729
00:25:12,413 --> 00:25:14,813
(The precious meat disappears before his eye.)

730
00:25:15,653 --> 00:25:16,653
(No!)

731
00:25:17,653 --> 00:25:19,522
(The Winking Cutie springs to action and picks up the grill.)

732
00:25:19,523 --> 00:25:20,692
Hurry!

733
00:25:20,693 --> 00:25:21,722
(Rescuing the meat)

734
00:25:21,723 --> 00:25:23,193
Hey, will you eat that?

735
00:25:23,493 --> 00:25:25,693
- Really? - We can rinse it.

736
00:25:26,733 --> 00:25:27,993
Will you eat that?

737
00:25:28,463 --> 00:25:29,933
We need to save it.

738
00:25:30,603 --> 00:25:32,002
It'll be a shame to waste it.

739
00:25:32,003 --> 00:25:33,202
(Covered in soot)

740
00:25:33,203 --> 00:25:35,872
Let's feed it to people who are rolling gimbap.

741
00:25:35,873 --> 00:25:37,073
(That's a good idea.)

742
00:25:37,843 --> 00:25:39,912
The mixed smell of rain and meat...

743
00:25:39,913 --> 00:25:41,512
gives us the proper camping vibes.

744
00:25:41,513 --> 00:25:43,582
People are coming out.

745
00:25:43,583 --> 00:25:46,352
Give the meat to them. Hurry up.

746
00:25:46,353 --> 00:25:48,183
(Enforcer, Park Ji Hoon)

747
00:25:48,983 --> 00:25:50,552
Give the meat to them. Hurry up.

748
00:25:50,553 --> 00:25:52,423
(Tongs operator, Ha Sung Woon)

749
00:25:52,953 --> 00:25:54,352
- Give it to them. - This is legit.

750
00:25:54,353 --> 00:25:56,063
(Wanna One's sparrow, Park Woo Jin)

751
00:25:56,523 --> 00:25:59,263
(Operation Soot-Covered Steak, Feed it to the gimbap rollers.)

752
00:25:59,633 --> 00:26:02,632
- This steak came out amazing. - Hey.

753
00:26:02,633 --> 00:26:04,462
- Seriously. - This is legit.

754
00:26:04,463 --> 00:26:05,902
You guys worked hard.

755
00:26:05,903 --> 00:26:07,372
- It's unbelievable. - What?

756
00:26:07,373 --> 00:26:08,672
- The steak. - The steak? Are you serious?

757
00:26:08,673 --> 00:26:09,772
I'm serious.

758
00:26:09,773 --> 00:26:11,472
(During that time, Sung Woon works on the meat.)

759
00:26:11,473 --> 00:26:13,342
Ji Sung, eat a piece.

760
00:26:13,343 --> 00:26:16,043
(The soot-covered steak goes into Ji Sung's mouth.)

761
00:26:16,683 --> 00:26:18,312
(Did he bite...)

762
00:26:18,313 --> 00:26:20,353
(the bait?)

763
00:26:22,983 --> 00:26:23,983
- Hey! - How is it?

764
00:26:23,984 --> 00:26:25,122
- It's insane. Yes. - Really?

765
00:26:25,123 --> 00:26:27,623
It was in the soot.

766
00:26:27,753 --> 00:26:28,893
Excuse me?

767
00:26:29,793 --> 00:26:31,422
- It's really tasty. - Isn't it tasty?

768
00:26:31,423 --> 00:26:33,393
Steak with soot.

769
00:26:33,593 --> 00:26:34,692
(Jae Hwan didn't hear about the steak with soot.)

770
00:26:34,693 --> 00:26:35,932
I want meat too.

771
00:26:35,933 --> 00:26:37,463
- Jae Hwan, do you want meat? - Yes.

772
00:26:38,803 --> 00:26:40,503
Try it and tell us how it is.

773
00:26:40,533 --> 00:26:42,342
Let's eat this instead of rice.

774
00:26:42,343 --> 00:26:43,643
- Is it tasty? - Yes.

775
00:26:43,703 --> 00:26:44,742
It was in the soot.

776
00:26:44,743 --> 00:26:46,073
